title: AWS S3: Requests
agents: aws
catalog: cloud/aws
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the number of get, put, delete, head,
 post, select and list requests made for objects in an AWS
 S3 bucket.

 To make this check work you have to configure the related
 special agent {Amazon Web Services (AWS)}.

 No default levels are set. Upper levels are configurable.

 You have to enable requests metrics in AWS/S3 console. This
 is a paid feature

item:
 Name of the instance

inventory:
 One service is created for each bucket if all required metrics
 (AllRequests) are given.
